@startuml Simple_DFD_Level_0_SkinSync
title Simple DFD Level 0 â€” SkinSync Booking System

' External entities
rectangle "Client" as Client
rectangle "Staff" as Staff
rectangle "Admin" as Admin
rectangle "Email/SMS Service" as Email
rectangle "GCash (external QR)" as GCash
rectangle "File Storage" as Files

' System boundary
rectangle "SkinSync System" as SkinSync

' Data stores
rectangle "Database (MySQL)" as DB

' Notes (explain terms used at Level 0)
note top
	"Assignments" = system assigns available staff to bookings.
	"Check-ins" = staff marks client arrival / attendance.
end note

' Data flows (high-level / consolidated)
Client --> SkinSync : Booking requests / Account updates / Inquiries
SkinSync --> Client : Confirmations / Notifications

Staff --> SkinSync : Availability / Check-ins / Assigned bookings
SkinSync --> Staff : Schedules / Assignments

Admin --> SkinSync : Management & Configuration
SkinSync --> Admin : Reports / Logs

' Payments: no external gateway used for card vault; GCash is external QR flow
SkinSync --> DB : Store saved card details (card vault - PCI scope note)
Client --> GCash : Scan QR to pay (external)
GCash --> Staff : Notify payment for confirmation

SkinSync --> Email : Send notifications (email / SMS)
SkinSync --> Files : Upload / Retrieve files (receipts, uploads)

SkinSync <--> DB : Read / Write (Users, Bookings, Services, Branches)

@enduml
